# JavaScript & TypeScript

## Formatting & Linting

- Use Biome when `biome.json` is present. Don't introduce Prettier/ESLint alongside it.
- If no Biome config exists, fall back to whatever formatter/linter the repo already uses.
- Don't add new lint rules or config files without asking.

## Package Management

- Detect the lockfile (`pnpm-lock.yaml`, `package-lock.json`, `yarn.lock`, `bun.lock`) and use the matching package manager.
- Never switch package managers in an existing project.

## Monorepos

- In Turborepo or workspace setups, run package-scoped checks before repo-wide ones.
- Respect workspace boundaries -- don't import across packages without checking `exports`/`dependencies`.

## Patterns

- Prefer named exports over default exports.
- Use `satisfies` for type narrowing when it improves readability.
- Keep barrel files (`index.ts`) thin -- re-export only, no logic.
- Use Zod for all external data validation.
- Handle loading and error states in UI components.

## Critical Rules

### Always

- Run type checking before committing (`bun run check`).
- Use Zod for all external data validation.
- Handle loading and error states in UI.

### Never

- Use `any` type -- use `unknown` and narrow.
- Skip error handling on async operations.
- Commit `.env` files -- use `.env.example`.
- Use `console.log` in production code -- use pino.
- Mutate props directly -- derive new values.

### Ask First

- Adding new dependencies.
- Changing database schema.
- Modifying auth flow.
- Deleting files.
